ZH: 不要乱写！

EN: Do not write randomly!

ZH: 他在试卷上乱写了一通。

EN: He scribbled all over the test paper.

ZH: 她在日记本上乱写了一些感想。

EN: She jotted down some thoughts in her diary.

ZH: 不要在公共场合乱写。

EN: Do not write randomly in public places.

ZH: 我发现他乱写了我的笔记本。

EN: I found that he scribbled in my notebook.

ZH: 他喜欢在纸上乱写乱画。

EN: He enjoys doodling and scribbling on paper.

ZH: 请你别再乱写了，规规矩矩地写字。

EN: Please stop scribbling and write neatly.

ZH: 他心情很不好，所以开始乱写了。

EN: He was in a bad mood, so he started to scribble.

ZH: 请不要再乱写乱画了。

EN: Please stop doodling and scribbling.

ZH: 孩子们在课本上乱写乱画。

EN: The children scribble in their textbooks.

ZH: 让学生注意不要在课本上乱写。

EN: Make sure the students do not scribble in their textbooks.

ZH: 老师看到他在课堂上乱写发火了。

EN: The teacher got angry when she saw him scribbling in class.

ZH: 我在记事本上乱写一通。

EN: I scribbled something in my notebook.

ZH: 别再在墙上乱写乱画。

EN: Stop scribbling on the wall.

ZH: 记得不要乱写别人的东西。

EN: Remember not to scribble on other people's things.

ZH: 我认真地写字，不会乱写。

EN: I write carefully and do not scribble.

ZH: 我的笔记被他乱写了。

EN: My notes were scribbled by him.

ZH: 别在书上乱写。

EN: Do not write randomly in the book.

ZH: 他乱写的字让我无法阅读。

EN: His scribbled words make it difficult for me to read.
